channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Guiding the generation of counterfactual explanations through temporal background knowledge for Predictive Process Monitoring
item.description: In this work, we adapt state-of-the-art techniques for counterfactual generation in the domain of XAI that are based on genetic algorithms to consider a series of temporal constraints at runtime.

item.title: Towards Generalizing to Unseen Domains with Few Labels
item.description: Existing domain generalization (DG) methods which are unable to exploit unlabeled data perform poorly compared to semi-supervised learning (SSL) methods under SSDG setting.

item.title: Benchmarking the Robustness of UAV Tracking Against Common Corruptions
item.description: Addressing this, we propose UAV-C, a large-scale benchmark for assessing robustness of UAV trackers under common corruptions.

item.title: Hierarchical Spatial Proximity Reasoning for Vision-and-Language Navigation
item.description: Most Vision-and-Language Navigation (VLN) algorithms tend to make decision errors, primarily due to a lack of visual common sense and insufficient reasoning capabilities.

item.title: Fed3DGS: Scalable 3D Gaussian Splatting with Federated Learning
item.description: In pursuit of a more scalable 3D reconstruction, we propose a federated learning framework with 3DGS, which is a decentralized framework and can potentially use distributed computational resources across millions of clients.

item.title: Align and Distill: Unifying and Improving Domain Adaptive Object Detection
item.description: We address these problems by introducing: (1) A unified benchmarking and implementation framework, Align and Distill (ALDI), enabling comparison of DAOD methods and supporting future development, (2) A fair and modern training and evaluation protocol for DAOD that addresses benchmarking pitfalls, (3) A new DAOD benchmark dataset, CFC-DAOD, enabling evaluation on diverse real-world data, and (4) A new method, ALDI++, that achieves state-of-the-art results by a large margin.

item.title: Open-World Semi-Supervised Learning for Node Classification
item.description: Open-world semi-supervised learning (Open-world SSL) for node classification, that classifies unlabeled nodes into seen classes or multiple novel classes, is a practical but under-explored problem in the graph community.

item.title: Boosting Continual Learning of Vision-Language Models via Mixture-of-Experts Adapters
item.description: Continual learning can empower vision-language models to continuously acquire new knowledge, without the need for access to the entire historical dataset.

item.title: MineDreamer: Learning to Follow Instructions via Chain-of-Imagination for Simulated-World Control
item.description: It is a long-lasting goal to design a generalist-embodied agent that can follow diverse instructions in human-like ways.

item.title: EchoReel: Enhancing Action Generation of Existing Video Diffusion Models

item.title: State-Separated SARSA: A Practical Sequential Decision-Making Algorithm with Recovering Rewards

item.title: VmambaIR: Visual State Space Model for Image Restoration
item.description: To address these challenges, we propose VmambaIR, which introduces State Space Models (SSMs) with linear complexity into comprehensive image restoration tasks.

item.title: Circle Representation for Medical Instance Object Segmentation
item.description: Recently, circle representation has been introduced for medical imaging, designed specifically to enhance the detection of instance objects that are spherically shaped (e. g., cells, glomeruli, and nuclei).

item.title: Probabilistic Calibration by Design for Neural Network Regression
item.description: To address the miscalibration issue of neural networks, various methods have been proposed to improve calibration, including post-hoc methods that adjust predictions after training and regularization methods that act during training.

item.description: In this work, we analyze the order-preserving ability on the whole search space (global) and a sub-space of top architectures (local), and empirically show that the local order-preserving for current two-stage NAS methods still need to be improved.

item.description: Biclustering, also called co-clustering, block clustering, or two-way clustering, involves the simultaneous clustering of both the rows and columns of a data matrix into distinct groups, such that the rows and columns within a group display similar patterns.
